# What additional measures can be taken by the United States to support Ukraine in the face of Russia's aggression?

## Summary
The United States is providing additional security assistance to Ukraine, including a sophisticated new air defense system <font color=#FF3399>[1,2]</font>. President Joe Biden is on the verge of approving nearly $45 billion in aid to Ukraine and NATO allies <font color=#FF3399>[3]</font> and has already sent more than $65 billion in humanitarian and military aid <font color=#FF3399>[2]</font>. Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky has arrived in the US to discuss these measures in person with President Biden at the Oval Office <font color=#FF3399>[4,5]</font>. This is a critical moment for Ukraine as the US is providing arms and weapons systems to save Ukraine but to also avoid escalating the conflict into a direct clash between NATO and Russia <font color=#FF3399>[5]</font>.

